President Biden addressed the United Auto Workers (UAW) at a picket line in Michigan. He praised the UAW for saving the automobile industry in 2008 and urged them to demand the raises and benefits they deserve. Shawn Fain, president of UAW Local 174, also spoke, emphasizing the importance of the working class in fighting corporate greed. Both President Biden and Fain highlighted the power of the working class and the need for economic and social justice. President Biden expressed support for the UAW's bargaining efforts and stated that the middle class and unions built the country.